---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Spatial Equity of Shared Micro-Mobility in Peripheral Neighborhoods"
  year="2023"
  category="Spatial Analysis · Urban Equity"
  tools={['Python', 'GeoPandas', 'SciPy', 'QGIS', 'Kernel Density Estimation', 'TAZ Analysis']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Background</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Shared e-scooter operators promised mobility access beyond the city center, but commercial
        incentives naturally pull fleets toward dense, high-demand zones, leaving peripheral
        neighborhoods underserved. This analysis tested whether that imbalance was happening in Tel
        Aviv's Quarter 7, a peripheral, socioeconomically mixed area.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Maps — Quarter 7 Distribution Analysis</h2>
    <div class="proj-map-grid">
      <div>
        <img
          src={`${base}/maps/scooter-kde-density.png`}
          alt="Kernel density map of shared e-scooter availability in Quarter 7, Tel Aviv"
          class="proj-map"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <p class="proj-map-caption">KDE surface — vehicle availability density across Quarter 7.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img
          src={`${base}/maps/scooter-kde-taz.png`}
          alt="TAZ-level vehicle count map for Quarter 7, Tel Aviv"
          class="proj-map"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <p class="proj-map-caption">Vehicle counts aggregated to Traffic Analysis Zones (TAZ).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Compiled vehicle-location snapshots from multiple operators via <strong>Populus</strong>.</li>
      <li>Modeled citywide availability with <strong>Kernel Density Estimation</strong> in <strong>SciPy</strong>, selecting bandwidth via cross-validation.</li>
      <li>Aggregated density surfaces to <strong>Traffic Analysis Zones (TAZ)</strong> with <strong>GeoPandas</strong>, then computed a supply-vs-demand ratio per zone using trip-origin density as a proxy for demand.</li>
      <li>Produced final classification and cartography in <strong>QGIS</strong>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Results</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Quarter 7 showed a clear deficit — despite strong trip-origin activity, vehicle availability
        lagged well behind central quarters with comparable demand. That evidence fed directly into
        redistribution requirements in the city's operator-licensing process.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
